folder: Murray Street & Church Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Murray street, north side, west from and including Church Street, The view shows the Sixth Ave., Elevated bending at Church and Murray Streets, to run west on Murray Street, for one block, to West Broadway, where it turns again to run North and South.

May 28, 1904.

Brown Brothers.

folder: Church Street & Murray Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Church Street, south from Murray Street, showing mainly "El" demolition. At this point this structure swings to the right, to continue westward to West Broadway. The station stairs barely discernible above the bus are at Park Place.

February 18, 1939

Gift of W. A. Lucas
